# üé¨ **SxzLib UI Library Documentary**

*A Comprehensive Guide for Roblox Developers*

---

## üìå **Introduction**

SxzLib is a **Lua-based UI library for Roblox** designed to help developers quickly build **interactive, visually appealing GUIs**. It allows you to create:

* Windows with draggable headers
* Tabs for content organization
* Interactive elements like buttons, toggles, sliders, labels, and inputs

Its modular design and easy-to-use callbacks make it perfect for public GUIs where scalability and user engagement matter.

---

## üß© **Core Utilities**

These are foundational functions used throughout the library:

| Function                        | Purpose                                                 |
| ------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| `Tween(obj, props, t)`          | Smoothly animates object properties                     |
| `Corner(obj, radius)`           | Adds rounded corners to UI elements                     |
| `Stroke(obj, color, thickness)` | Adds borders to UI elements                             |
| `New(class, props, parent)`     | Creates a new instance with given properties and parent |

These utilities simplify GUI creation, animation, and styling.

---

## ü™ü **Creating Windows**

```lua
local Window = SxzLib:CreateWindow({
    Title = "SXZ Hub",
    SubTitle = "Dev: @author",
    Icon = "‚öî",
    Color = Color3.fromRGB(60,100,220),
    Size = Vector2.new(420, 310)
})
```

**Key Features:**

* Draggable header with smooth animation
* Float button to toggle visibility
* Sidebar for tabs
* Search box for filtering tabs
* Resizable content area

---

## üóÇÔ∏è **Tabs**

Tabs organize UI content. Each tab includes:

* Sidebar button
* Independent content holder

Example:

```lua
local tab = Window:CreateTab("Main", "‚≠ê")
```

Tabs allow developers to categorize controls and improve UX in large GUIs.

---

## üîò **UI Elements**

### Toggle

```lua
tab:Toggle({
    Name = "Enable Feature",
    Description = "Turns a feature on or off",
    Default = false,
    Callback = function(state)
        print("Toggled:", state)
    end
})
```

---

### Slider

```lua
tab:Slider({
    Name = "Speed",
    Min = 1,
    Max = 100,
    Default = 50,
    Callback = function(value)
        print("Value:", value)
    end
})
```

---

### Button

```lua
tab:Button({
    Name = "Press Me",
    Callback = function()
        print("Button clicked")
    end
})
```

---

### Input

```lua
tab:Input({
    Name = "Enter Text",
    Placeholder = "Type here...",
    Callback = function(text)
        print("Input:", text)
    end
})
```

---

### Label & Separator

```lua
tab:Label("Welcome to SXZ Hub")
tab:Separator()
```

* Labels display static text
* Separators create visual divisions

---

## üöÄ **Full Example**

```lua
local Window = SxzLib:CreateWindow({
    Title = "SXZ Hub",
    SubTitle = "By @Dev",
    Color = Color3.fromRGB(100,60,200)
})

local mainTab = Window:CreateTab("Main", "‚≠ê")
mainTab:Label("Welcome!")
mainTab:Toggle({
    Name = "Activate Mode",
    Default = false,
    Callback = print
})
mainTab:Slider({
    Name = "Speed",
    Min = 1,
    Max = 100,
    Default = 50,
    Callback = print
})
mainTab:Button({
    Name = "Test",
    Callback = function() print("Test clicked!") end
})
```

---

## üõ†Ô∏è **Advanced Tips**

* Store control references for later use
* Combine multiple tabs for complex UIs
* Use callbacks to trigger in-game actions
* Customize colors, fonts, and sizes for a unique theme

---

## üèÅ **Conclusion**

SxzLib is ideal for **public GUIs**, developer tools, dashboards, and in-game menus. Its simple API, drag-and-drop capability, and modular structure make it scalable for **high-traffic use**.

Whether for a **developer hub**, **debug panel**, or **interactive game menu**, SxzLib provides everything needed to build polished Roblox interfaces.
